:{"found":true,"entry_count":7,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":13},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2588","n2594","n2595","n2596"]}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"human"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"humans, humankind","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"skin, outer skin, epidermis","tags":["collective"],"examples":[{"text":"سَأُصْلِيهِ سَقَرَ / وَمَا أَدْرَاكَ مَا سَقَرُ / لَا تُبْقِي وَلَا تَذَرُ / لَوَّاحَةٌ لِلْبَشَرِ / عَلَيْهَا تِسْعَةَ عَشَرَ","english":"I shall cast thee into the hellfire. And what shall acquaint you with what the hellfire be? Neither does it preserve nor does it spare. Scorching the skins. Over it are nineteen [angels guarding]."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to peel, to pare"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to shave so as to render the skin visible"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to eat the ground bare"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to take (a matter) into one's own hands"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of بَشَرَ (bašara) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to rejoice at, to become glad, to congratulate, to rejoice"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of بَشِرَ (bašira) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of بَشَرَ (bašara) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to bring good news (to)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to evangelize, to preach the gospel (to)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-West Semitic *baśar- (“flesh, human body”). The original meaning \"flesh\" was replaced by لَحْم (laḥm).\n\nRelated to بَشَر (bašar, “skin”) as rejoicement manifests itself as a complexion of the skin.\n\nCausative of بَشِرَ (bašira, “to rejoice at”). Religious sense is a literal translation of Ancient Greek εὐαγγελίζω (euangelízō), from εὐαγγέλιον (euangélion, “good news, gospel”). Cognate with Hebrew בִּשֵׂר (bisér, biśśēr, “to bring good news”)."}